cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new approach to address the non-stationarity of the environment in multi-agent reinforcement learning systems by utilizing a deep net critic. It also involves the use of permutation invariant techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning. Additionally, it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as it deals with multi-agent reinforcement learning. It could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves the use of reinforcement learning in controlling multi-agent systems.
